CHATEAU MARGAUX 1947 (Margaux)

If one were to choose the greatest postwar Claret, Chateau Margaux 1947 would have to be considered a leading contestant. Not commercially available for years, it has rested, untouched, in the cellars of Chateau Margaux since its bottling in 1949 until this year when it was shipped to New York. It is here in all its glory to add its perfection to any wine collection.
